sequenceDiagram
    participant Client as External Client
    participant Route as OpenShift Route<br/>80/TCP HTTP
    participant Service as TrustyAI Service<br/>8080/TCP HTTP
    participant Reconciler as KServe Inference<br/>Payload Reconciler
    participant Storage as Storage Backend<br/>(PVC/DB/MinIO)
    participant ModelMesh as KServe / ModelMesh<br/>Model Server
    participant KServeIS as KServe InferenceService<br/>(CloudEvents)
    participant Prometheus as Prometheus<br/>OpenShift Monitoring
    participant MariaDB as MariaDB/MySQL<br/>3306/TCP JDBC

    Note over Client,Prometheus: Flow 1: Inference Payload Ingestion (ModelMesh → TrustyAI)
    ModelMesh->>Service: POST /consumer/kserve/v2<br/>HTTP/8080 InferencePartialPayload
    Service->>Reconciler: Match request ↔ response
    Reconciler->>Storage: Persist complete observation
    Note right of Storage: PVC: filesystem /inputs<br/>DB: JDBC/3306<br/>MinIO: S3 API

    Note over Client,Prometheus: Flow 2: CloudEvents Payload Ingestion (KServe → TrustyAI)
    KServeIS->>Service: CloudEvent POST<br/>org.kubeflow.serving.inference.request<br/>HTTP/8080
    KServeIS->>Service: CloudEvent POST<br/>org.kubeflow.serving.inference.response<br/>HTTP/8080
    Service->>Reconciler: Match request ↔ response
    Reconciler->>Storage: Persist complete observation

    Note over Client,Prometheus: Flow 3: Fairness/Drift Metric Computation
    Client->>Route: POST /metrics/group/fairness/spd<br/>HTTP/80
    Route->>Service: Forward HTTP/8080
    Service->>Storage: Read observation data
    Storage-->>Service: DataFrame
    Service->>Service: Compute metric (SPD/DIR/KSTest/etc.)
    Service->>Service: Register with PrometheusScheduler
    Service-->>Route: Metric result JSON
    Route-->>Client: Response

    loop Every 5s (configurable)
        Service->>Service: PrometheusScheduler computes<br/>all registered metrics
        Service->>Service: Publish to Micrometer gauges<br/>(trustyai_spd, trustyai_dir)
    end

    Prometheus->>Service: GET /q/metrics<br/>HTTP/8080<br/>Auth: Bearer Token (SA)
    Service-->>Prometheus: Prometheus exposition format<br/>(trustyai_* gauges)

    Note over Client,Prometheus: Flow 4: Explainability Request (ODH only, disabled in RHOAI)
    Client->>Route: POST /explainers/local/lime<br/>HTTP/80
    Route->>Service: Forward HTTP/8080
    Service->>Storage: Load observation data
    Storage-->>Service: DataFrame
    Service->>ModelMesh: KServe v2 HTTP inference<br/>POST /v2/models/{model}/infer<br/>HTTP/8080
    ModelMesh-->>Service: Inference result
    Note right of Service: Alternative: gRPC v2<br/>plaintext (no TLS)
    Service->>Service: Run LIME/SHAP/CF algorithm<br/>(explainability-core)
    Service-->>Route: Explanation result JSON
    Route-->>Client: Response

    Note over Client,Prometheus: Flow 5: Data Upload
    Client->>Route: POST /data/upload<br/>HTTP/80
    Route->>Service: Forward HTTP/8080
    Service->>Storage: Persist batch data / ground truths
    Service-->>Route: Upload confirmation
    Route-->>Client: Response
